{
  "texts": [
    "This procedure ensures the system is equipped with a kernel that is optimized for real-time applications, enhancing the predictability and responsiveness of tasks critical in real-time computing environments.For detailed guidance and the latest versions of the kernel and PREEMPT RT patch, the official Linux kernel website [106] and the PREEMPT RT section on the Linux Foundation's website [107] are recommended as primary resources.",
    "Execution Time MeasurementTo measure the execution time, chrono::high resolution clock::now() [108] is used as a timestamp function, which is commonly employed to measure the execution time of various functions.",
    "To isolate the execution time of the code under measurement, we should subtract the timestamp function's overhead from the measured time.",
    "Therefore, as an initial step, we conducted an experiment to quantify the overhead associated with capturing system time.In this experiment, the overhead of the timestamp function is measured several times in a loop to account for randomness.",
    "As a result, the overhead of loop should be deducted from the overall time measured."
  ]
}